==English==
===Pronunciation===

:laz' yur ite

===Etymology===

:Named for the distinctive blue coloration.

===Noun===
'''Lazurite'''

#A [[mineral]] of metamorphosed [[limestone]]s. Lazurite forms the gemstone ''Lapis Lazuli'', and crushed Lazurite provided the ''ultramarine'' color in artists' paint of the old masters.  [[Sodalite]] and Lazurite form the ''Sodalite Group'' of silicate minerals.

=== Chemical composition ===
*Sodium aluminum silicate with sulphur, <math>Na_{4-5}Al_3Si_3O_{12}S</math>
 
=== Physical properties ===

*Moh's Hardness: 5.0-5.5
*Specific gravity: 2.4-2.5
*Color: Blue, violet-blue, greenish-blue
*Luster: Glassy, translucent
*Fracture: Uneven
*Cleavage: Poor dodecahedral
*Habit: Cubic-hexoctahedral

